org.opendaylight.yang.gen.v1.urn.onf.core.network.module.rev160630

Interface GLayerProtocol

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataContainer, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataObject
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LpList

    public interface GLayerProtocol
extends org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataObject

    This class represents the following YANG schema fragment defined in module onf-core-network-module 

     grouping G_LayerProtocol {
     leaf layerProtocolName {
         type LayerProtocolName;
     }
     container lpSpec {
         container adapterSpec {
             uses G_ConnectionPointAndAdapterSpec;
         }
         container terminationSpec {
             uses G_TerminationSpec;
         }
         list adapterPropertySpecList {
             key "uuid"
             leaf uuid {
                 type string;
             }
             uses G_AdapterPropertySpec;
         }
         container providerViewSpec {
             uses G_ProviderViewSpec;
         }
         list serverSpecList {
             key "uuid"
             leaf uuid {
                 type string;
             }
             uses G_ServerSpec;
         }
         uses G_LayerProtocolSpec;
     }
     leaf configuredClientCapacity {
         type string;
     }
     leaf lpDirection {
         type TerminationDirection;
     }
     leaf terminationState {
         type string;
     }
 }
    The schema path to identify an instance is onf-core-network-module/G_LayerProtocol

      The LpSpec identifies the internal structure of the LP explaining internal flexibilities, degreeof termination and degree of adaptation on both client and server side.
